Adjust rack to middle position (top and middle positions for 8 servings) and
preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil.
(TIP: Start with hot tap water for faster boiling.) Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @zucchini{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise) lengthwise; slice
crosswise into ¼-inch-thick quarter-moons.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{12%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water
(2 cups for 8 servings), then drain. Keep empty pot handy for Step 4.

While pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan
over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{20%ounce}, zucchini, @Italian seasoning{2%tablespoon},
@garlic powder{2%teaspoon}, a big pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.

Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until zucchini is tender and beef is cooked
through, ~{5-7%minutes}. (For 8 servings, work in batches, adding a drizzle of
oil between batches.)

Remove pan from heat.
> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Transfer beef mixture to pot used for pasta; add @marinara{14%ounce},
@tomato paste{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{3}, and ½ cup reserved pasta
cooking water (1 cup for 8 servings). Bring to a boil over medium-high heat;
cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is slightly thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}.
> TIP: If sauce is too thick, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time.

Turn off heat; add drained penne to pot with sauce and stir to combine. Taste
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Transfer pasta to a lightly oiled #9-by-13-inch baking dish{} (use 2 lightly
oiled 9-by-13-inch baking dishes for 8 servings). Carefully dollop
@ricotta cheese{8%ounce} all over pasta and top with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Bake, uncovered, on middle rack until cheese is melted, ~{10-12%minutes}
(for 8 servings, bake on top and middle racks, switching rack positions
halfway through).

Increase oven temperature to broil; bake until cheese is browned,
~{2-3%minutes} more.
> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Let baked penne cool for ~{5%minutes} before serving. Sprinkle with as many
@chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve family style.

> Ground beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.